parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of an accident can lead to serious injury or even death.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in the event of an accident
despite meeting the necessary deployment criteria.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended airbag deployment can cause injuries and distractions while driving, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Airbags deploy without any apparent reason
such as a crash or impact.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the SRS (Supplemental Restraint System) light can lead to airbag system failures, increasing the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The SRS light comes on intermittently or stays on
indicating a problem with the airbag system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A vehicle fire can cause serious injury or death, as well as property damage.
symptoms: The vehicle catches on fire
potentially due to a faulty oil filter or other mechanical issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Spontaneous windshield cracking can reduce visibility, causing accidents or accidents, and may lead to costly repairs.
symptoms: Windshield cracks suddenly
without any apparent impact or damage
often in the lower sections of the windshield.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Poor windshield quality or design can lead to increased risk of cracking or shattering, compromising driver safety and visibility.
symptoms: Small impacts
such as sand or gravel
cause significant cracks or damage to the windshield
which may spread rapidly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The thumping noise and discomfort caused by opening the rear window at high speeds can distract the driver, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Opening the rear window at speeds above 40mph causes a loud thumping noise
increasing in intensity with speed
and resulting in physical discomfort or pain.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped rear brake rotors can cause a pulsating sensation when braking, leading to reduced stopping power and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Pulsating or vibrating sensation when braking
warped brake rotors
brake noise
brake pads wear unevenly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive brake noise and vibration can be a sign of a larger problem with the brake system, potentially leading to reduced stopping power and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Loud popping or grinding noise when applying brakes
vibration when braking
brake pads wear unevenly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature brake wear and failure can lead to reduced stopping power and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Brake pads wear unevenly
brake rotors warp or wear excessively
frequent brake repairs or replacements.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Automatic Transmission Failure to Engage Park
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic transmission to engage park can cause the vehicle to move unexpectedly, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle moves on its own after the key is turned off and removed
the transmission remains in drive even after the key is removed
the vehicle does not engage park when the transmission is shifted into park.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended downshifting of the automatic transmission can cause loss of control, accidents, or near-miss situations, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The transmission shifts from a higher gear to a lower gear without warning
the transmission shifts erratically
the vehicle experiences sudden loss of power or acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The premature failure of the automatic transmission can cause unexpected breakdowns, leaving the driver stranded, and potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The transmission fails to engage gears
the transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle experiences loss of power or acceleration
the transmission warning light illuminates.
